Rustenburg - Four men were arrested after a truck was set alight and two cars damaged in Majakaneng south of Brits on Wednesday, North West police said.&#x201C;It is alleged that passing motorists were pelted with stones and that led to damages of two vehicles while the third one, a truck was burnt,&#x201D; said Brigadier Sabata Mokgwabone.Mokgwabone said the four men are expected to appear in court soon facing a charge of public violence.He said the police were monitoring the situation at Majakaneng where some members of the community barricaded N4 road near Sun City off-ramp.Community members apparently barricaded the road after they were evicted from privately own farm land they had been illegally occupied. African News Agency IOL News on Facebook IOL on Twitter